        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "We’re not saying the C8 Corvette has an ugly body, but this version looks far more aggressive and dramatic, putting it in league with hypercars like the Koenigsegg Agera. The whole point of the Corvette has always been accessible performance, so don’t hold your breath on GM using anything from this for the C9. With a mere 24 Ares S1 Project cars planned, there’s no doubt these will be far more expensive than any C8 on the market.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/09/Motorious---4--12.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "photo credit: Ares Design"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "All the body panels are crafted by hand from carbon fiber. With the low-slung profile, prominent wheel arches, and the expanse of glass wrapping from the front to sides, it looks nothing like a Corvette. The cockpit sits far forward and the hood slopes rapidly forward to a low front splitter, plus the side mirrors extend out like those on many of today’s hypercars. Designers even placed dual exhaust tips in the rear engine cover, not in the massive diffuser.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/09/Motorious---2--22.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "photo credit: Ares Design"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "You’ll also note the extensive venting in the fenders, hood, and roof. There’s also a dynamic rear spoiler According to Ares, the wild design wasn’t created just to catch the eye. It’s also optimized for aerodynamics and stability, we’re assuming especially for pushing the C8 on a track’s long straightaway.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "caption": "photo credit: Ares Design",
